"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

Happy Monday. It's a new week of politics and a new monologue. Scott Walker enters the massive GOP presidential race. Can he pull attention away from the circus that is Donald Trump?

Tonight's panel consists of JEDIDIAH BILA, ANDY LEVY, and JANICE DEAN. They continue to talk about Scott Walker. His chances, his social conservatism, and his union busting ways. Marine Vet and Democrat Jim Webb is throwing his hat into the presidential ring. He thinks his fellow Democrats are too liberal.

Our pretty party panel returns to talk about 2016 candidates being done with Donald Trump. Christie hates 'em, Jeb is done with 'em. Could this be why he's polling at second place? Stresiand effect as applied to presidential politics. 

Hillary has laid out her economic plan. She's big on things being "fair". JOHNATHAN HOENIG is here via satellite to discuss. Some pretty hyperbolic language used by our guest, but then again he is billed as the "Capitalist Pig Hedge Fund Founder".

TOPICAL STORM:
David Letterman does a Donald Trump top 10 list.
Danica Patrick spares no insults after being rear ended by Dale Earnhardt Jr.
Taylor Swift reserves the right to injure photographers.
Guy drops shovel, makes Nirvana song.
Brian Cranston drops the mic at Comic-con.

TODAY IS NATIONAL FRENCH FRY DAY! It's our first annual french fry test here on Kennedy. She does a blind taste test. Nails each one, gets messed up hair. Smart Cities are on the way. How long is it before privacy becomes a fuzzy memory?

MATT BESSER of the Upright Citizens Brigade is here via satellite to talk about the California drought, celebrities with palatial green estates surrounded by deserts, his podcast "Improv for Humans", and snitching on his neighbors.

JANICE DEAN returns sans the party panel to talk about her kids book "Freddy the Frogcaster".
